**assistant**:
> If your drain pipe goes from the garbage disposal into a metal fitting and you don't see any visible way to loosen it from the plastic pipe, it's possible that the connection is a bit more complex. In this case, it might be best to call a professional plumber to assist you.
> 
> However, if you're feeling confident and want to try one more step, you could attempt using a pipe wrench to loosen the metal fitting. 
> 
> Here's how you can give it a try:
> 
> 1. **Prepare the area:** Start by placing a bucket or a towel under the pipe connection to catch any water or debris that may come out.
> 
> 2. **Use a pipe wrench:** Take a pipe wrench or a pair of pliers and grip the metal fitting securely. Turn the fitting counterclockwise to attempt to loosen it. Be careful not to force it too hard or use excessive pressure, as this could cause damage.
> 
> 3. **Apply lubricant:** If the metal fitting seems stuck or resistant to turning, you could try applying a lubricant such as WD-40 to the connection. Let it sit for a few minutes to penetrate and then try loosening it again.
> 
> If, despite your best efforts, you're unable to loosen the metal fitting or if you encounter any difficulties during the process, it's recommended to call a professional plumber. They have the expertise and specialized tools to handle more complex plumbing situations and can ensure the job is done safely and correctly.
